-- Turkey Says 2,500 Syrians Cross Border in Biggest Exodus to Date
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-06T07:31:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/turkey-says-2-500-syrians-cross-border-in-biggest-exodus-to-date.html
About 2,500 Syrians crossed into
 Turkey  in the past 24 hours in the biggest exodus from violence
in Syria to date, Turkish Foreign Minister  Ahmet Davutoglu  told
United Nations Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon in a phone call
today.  Syrians are fleeing military operations using helicopters
near the border and crossed into Turkey close to the city of
Reyhanli, Davutoglu said in a phone call to Ban at 2:00 a.m.
local time, according to Turkeyâ€™s state-run Anatolia news
agency.  Davutoglu stressed that the situation was urgent and
invited UN officials to monitor developments from the Turkish
border, Anatolia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
